<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand what drives the Zillmere buyer pool. This is a suburb where accurate pricing and confident presentation matter enormously, because buyers shopping here are comparing a wide range of options across the northern corridor simultaneously. A property that stands out for presentation and is positioned accurately does not sit.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Zillmere market is shaped by its adjacency to Aspley, one of the northern corridor's most consistently in-demand family suburbs. Buyers who miss out in Aspley or find its price point just out of reach look immediately to Zillmere, Virginia and Geebung. This spill-over dynamic means that when Aspley clearance rates are high, Zillmere vendor conditions tend to follow. Streets closer to Zillmere station and the Aspley boundary consistently attract more buyer interest than those further south toward the Virginia industrial fringe. Post-war homes on 600-plus square metre blocks remain the strongest-performing property type in this suburb.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Northern Brisbane Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Train access to CBD via Shorncliffe line</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
